{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token function\">getSelection</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"parameters","title":"Parameters","isH3":true,"content":"<p>None.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"return_value","title":"Return value","isH3":true,"content":"<p>A <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a> object.</p>\n<p>\n  When cast to string, either by appending an empty string (<code>\"\"</code>) or using\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection/toString\"><code>Selection.toString()</code></a>, this object returns the text selected.\n</p>\n<p>\n  When called on an <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/iframe\"><code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code></a> that is not displayed (e.g., where\n  <code>display: none</code> is set) Firefox will return <code>null</code>, whereas other\n  browsers will return a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a> object with\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection/type\"><code>Selection.type</code></a> set to <code>None</code>.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">foo</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> selObj <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> window<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getSelection</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token function\">alert</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>selObj<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> selRange <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> selObj<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">getRangeAt</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">0</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// do stuff with the range</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"string_representation_of_the_selection_object","title":"String representation of the Selection object","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  In JavaScript, when an object is passed to a function expecting a string (like <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/alert\"><code>window.alert()</code></a> or <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/write\"><code>document.write()</code></a>), the object's\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/toString\"><code>toString()</code></a> method is called and the returned value is\n  passed to the function. This can make the object appear to be a string when used with\n  other functions when it is really an object with properties and methods.\n</p>\n<p>\n  In the above example, <code>selObj.toString()</code> is automatically called when it is\n  passed to <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/alert\"><code>window.alert()</code></a>. However, attempting to use a JavaScript <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String\">String</a> property\n  or method such as\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/length\"><code>length</code></a>\n  or\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String/substr\"><code>substr</code></a>\n  directly on a <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a> object will result in an error if it does not\n  have that property or method and may return unexpected results if it does. To use a\n  <code>Selection</code> object as a string, call its <code>toString()</code> method\n  directly:\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><p class=\"example-header\"><span class=\"language-name\">js</span></p><pre class=\"brush: js notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> selectedText <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> selObj<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n  <li><code>selObj</code> is a <code>Selection</code> object.</li>\n  <li><code>selectedText</code> is a string (Selected text).</li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"related_objects","title":"Related objects","isH3":true,"content":"<p>\n  You can call <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/getSelection\"><code>Document.getSelection()</code></a>, which works identically to\n  <code>Window.getSelection()</code>.\n</p>\n<p>\n  It is worth noting that currently <code>getSelection()</code> doesn't work on the\n  content of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/textarea\"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a> and <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/input\"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a> elements in Firefox\n  and Edge (Legacy). <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLInputElement/setSelectionRange\"><code>HTMLInputElement.setSelectionRange()</code></a>\n  or the <code>selectionStart</code> and <code>selectionEnd</code> properties could be\n  used to work around this.\n</p>\n<p>\n  Notice also the difference between <em>selection</em> and <em>focus</em>.\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/activeElement\"><code>Document.activeElement</code></a> returns the focused element.\n</p>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://w3c.github.io/selection-api/#dom-window-getselection","title":"Selection API"}],"query":"api.Window.getSelection"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.Window.getSelection"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\">Selection API</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Selection\"><code>Selection</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Range\"><code>Range</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Document/getSelection\"><code>Document.getSelection()</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLInputElement/setSelectionRange\"><code>HTMLInputElement.setSelectionRange()</code></a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Notes","id":"notes"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The Window.getSelection() method returns a\n  Selection object representing the range of text selected by the user or\n  the current position of the caret.","popularity":0.0202,"modified":"2023-04-08T06:57:07.000Z","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/window/getselection","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/window/getselection/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/cc070123f72376faec06e36622c4fc723a75325f","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"getSelection()","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window","title":"Window"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/getSelection","title":"getSelection()"}],"pageTitle":"Window: getSelection() method - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false}}